    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>People who carve, engrave, or otherwise decorate or create objects made from horn, which is material derived from outgrowths of compacted skin or hair on the heads of animals, often from cows. Examples include combs, cups, spoons, handles, and adornments. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
